  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "35 migrants arrested in Panadura",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Sri Lanka Navy has arrested 35 Sri Lankan migrants in the waters off Panadura while attempting to sail to Australia illegally on a dilapidated multi-day trawler.",
        "Among the group were 25 men, 04 women and 06 children, Navy Media Spokesman Capt. Indika de Silva said.",
        "A search operation conducted in the seas off Panadura yesterday evening revealed that a suspicious multi-day trawler had been intercepted and apprehended during a search operation, the Navy spokesman said.",
        "The Navy further inspected the vessel and observed a technical defect in its engine, which was said to be unsuitable for a long sea voyage."
      ],
